{"id":14881244,"mediaExerciseId":"1ce7cd2c-cf53-49fd-8ff4-52d258320fca","exerciseName":"10","chapterName":"10","chapterTitle":"Making Capital Investment Decisions","groupId":612342,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":343,"solutions":[{"id":6298427,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will solve for the net present value of the project based on the given required return\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The net present value (NPV) refers to the difference between the inflow and outflow of cash in a given project. This can be solved using the formula:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Net present value}&=\\dfrac{\\text{Cashflow}}{(1+\\text{expected return})^\\text{time}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"ubstituting the cashflow value of $\\$1,019,550$, the expected return rate of $0.12\\$ and time of $3$ years, the net present value will be:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Net present value}&=\\dfrac{\\$1,019,550}{(1+0.12)^{3}}\\\\[15 pt]\n&= \\$725,695.55 \n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe net present value of this project is $\\$725,695.55$\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"7a285b17-7f2c-41ab-83f7-871a5ef54bea","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPr